About the Chair

   The Energy and Prosperity academic Chair was created in 2015 to inform
   decisions of public and private actors in managing the energy
   transition. The Chair research deals with the impacts of energy
   transition on national economies (growth, employment, debt), on
   specific sectors (transportation, construction, energy , finance) and
   with the associated financing issues. Hosted by the Risk Foundation,
   the chair has the support of ADEME, Air Liquide, the French Development
   Agency, the Caisse des Dépôts, Mirova , Schneider Electric and SNCF .

Co-directors quotes

   [photo_co_directeurs.jpg]

Quote Jean-Pierre Ponssard :

Quote Gaël Giraud :

   « The energy transition is a global societal project, which impacts all
   economic sectors »

   « The real role of energy and the limits of the Anthropocene will lead
   economists to change their paradigm »

